Question 2
QX||PN|South,West,North,East|ST||MD|2,S Q76H KJ6D AK87C K32,,S52HA4D 653C J109865|sv|o|rh||AH|Question 2|mb|1n2s2np3cppp|lb|*mWith the hands and auction above, what convention do East-West seem to be employing?^Unusual Notrump~Puppet Stayman~Relay-Control steps~Lebensohl~other^4|at|^B@2
Lebensohl. This convention uses a 2NT bid by responder (after a 1NT opening is overcalled) to relay to 3@C (either to play, or as the start of a different description).|
