^-|ht|e|fp||at|^B@2The bidding is|
ht|e|cs|6|at|^l{|ia|1sp3sp5d|at|}|ht|d|cs||at|^kQuestion 3 - by Larry Cohen|hf|j|lb|*mWhat convention is West using if his 5D bid asks East how many of these 4 cards he holds: SA,SK, HA, CA?^Roman Keycard Blackwood~Splinter Asks~Relay Step-Asking~Exclusion Keycard Blackwood~Splinter Bids^4|
ht|l|at|^B@2
Exclusion Keycard Blackwood. A jump above game (after a trump suit is agreed) is used to ask for Keycards excluding the suit jumped into. West might hold: @S AQJ1076  @H K2 @C KQJ62.|
